This paper focuses on depth estimation for robotic tasks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes an efficient and lightweight neural network architecture, which involves techniques such as network pruning, that are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed network in terms of speed and accuracy, which are key metrics in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
